pe">Selling with BuynBrag</a></li><li><a href="" scroll-to="" hash="sellerRegistration" class="ng-isolate-scope">Seller Registration</a></li><li><a href="" scroll-to="" hash="sellerPolicy" class="ng-isolate-scope">Rule and Policies</a></li></ul></div><div class="span9" data-spy="scroll" data-target=".affixSidebar"><section id="sellingOverview"><h3 class="heading topMar0">Selling with BuynBrag</h3><article class="descriptionContainer"><p>BuynBrag is a marketplace of unique, curated finds from across the country. We troll the bylanes of towns small and big, in the search for things that are crafted with love and tell a story.</p><p>We invite the creators of these finds to set up shop with us and make it available to others who share our sense of aesthetic, who would appreciate it as much as us.</p><p>You can set up a store on BuynBrag if you are one of the following:</p><ul><li>You have a boutique store</li><li>You have an e-commerce website</li><li>You supply products to various stores</li><li>You help artisans and designers sell their products</li></ul><h4>The BuynBrag Advantage:</h4><p>At Buynbrag, we believe in providing you the complete solution for taking your business online. To sell online, you do not have to set up a website, you just need an e-store. We provide you that and lots more and you do what you do best, i.e. create amazing products.</p><p>What's more, you sell your creations under your own brand across the country to discerning shoppers who seek quality craftsmanship and unique design.</p><p>When an order comes in, we pick it up from your warehouse and have it delivered at the shopper's doorstep.</p><h5>Therefore we take over complete responsibility for:</h5><ul style="padding:10px 0px 0px 15px"><li>Designing your Virtual Storefront</li><li>Product Photography (optional)</li><li>Content Writing (optional)</li><li>Inventory Planning</li><li>Pricing</li><li>Store Management</li><li>Logistics Support</li><li>Customer Care</li><li>Marketing and Promotions</li></ul></article></section><section id="sellerRegistration"><h3 class="heading">Seller Registration</h3><article class="descriptionContainer"><p>If you think your products fit the bill, give us a shout</p><p>Email us at&nbsp;<span><a href="mailto:seller@buynbrag.com" target="_top">seller@buynbrag.com</a></span>&nbsp;with the following details.</p><ul><li>A brief description of your business</li><li>Location of business</li><li>Product photographs</li><li>Business owner's bio</li></ul><p>Someone from our team will be in touch with you to take things forward.</p></article></section><section id="sellerPolicy"><h3 class="heading">General User Policy</h3><article class="descriptionContainer"><div class="rightPanelDesc paddingBottom8"><strong>1. General Policies and Rules</strong></div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>1.1</strong> BuynBrag’ss policies and rules are the common guidelines that create a safe, trusted and fair trading environment for all BuynBrag.com users. To promote a safe and trusted trading environment, BuynBrag.com enforces these polices and rules.</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>1.2</strong> User MoU. This is the most important BuynBrag.com policy and rule document. All users are responsible for reviewing and understanding BuynBrag’s policies and all applicable laws and regulations contained in this legal contract.</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>1.3</strong> Rules for Everyone. General policies applying to all BuynBrag.com members, Company’s employees and BuynBrag.com. This section includes rules that protect your privacy and your identity. Learn more about issues like the use of profanity, unsolicited email (spam) etc.</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>1.4</strong> Prohibited and Restricted Items. There are many items that are restricted to sell online at BuynBrag.com, such as liquor, adult content/material, banned items such as ivory etc? Find out in our comprehensive list of banned and restricted items.</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>1.5</strong> Keyword Spamming Policy. This policy is designed to restrict Sellers not to abuse brand names as keywords in product listings to drive attention.</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>1.6</strong> Links Policy − This policy is designed to restrict Sellers to inappropriately add links in its product listings or online storefront to move traffic away from BuynBrag.</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom18"><strong>1.7</strong> Rules about Intellectual Property. BuynBrag.com has zero tolerance for any intellectual property violations. Please notify us in case any violation has occurred without our knowledge and we will take appropriate action as soon as possible.</div><div class="rightPanelDesc paddingBottom8"><strong>2. BuynBrag rules and policies are designed to:</strong></div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>•</strong> Minimize risks to both buyers and sellers</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>•</strong> Support government laws and regulations</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>•</strong> Provide equal opportunity to all buyers and seller</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>•</strong> Protect intellectual property rights</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>•</strong> Provide an enjoyable buying experience</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Support the values of the BuynBrag.com Community</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom18">Please learn more about BuynBrag’s policies that will help you avoid breaking rules (including the law) and help you in trading with reliable, trustworthy buyers and sellers.</div><div class="rightPanelDesc paddingBottom8"><strong>3. Violations of policy may result in a range of actions including:</strong></div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>•</strong> Listing cancellation</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>•</strong> Store suspension</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>•</strong> Limits on account privileges</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>•</strong> Account suspension</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Loss of Top Rated Seller status</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom18"><strong>Note:</strong> You may contact BuynBrag.com to report violations by using the Contact usï¿½ link found on most policy pages.</div><div class="rightPanelDesc paddingBottom8"><strong>4. Prohibited and Restricted Items</strong></div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8">Following items are not allowed to be sold online at BuynBrag.com. Please note that Sellers/sellers are responsible for any legal issues and other liabilities arising if you try and sell these items at BuynBrag.com. We will cancel the listing of prohibited and restricted items within 24 hours after we come to know about such occurrence.</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>•</strong> Adult Material (also see Mature Audiences)</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>•</strong> Alcohol (also see Wine)</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>•</strong> Animals and Wildlife Products − examples include live animals, mounted specimens, and ivory</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>•</strong> Artifacts</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Beta Software</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Bootleg/Pirated Recordings</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Brand Name Misuse</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Catalogue and URL Sales</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Clothing (used/not new)</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Comparison Policy</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Compilation and Informational Media</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>•</strong> Contact Information</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Contracts</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Copyrights</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Counterfeit Currency and Stamps</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Downloadable Media</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Drugs</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Electronic Surveillance Equipment</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Embargoed Goods and Prohibited Countries</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>•</strong> Event Tickets</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Firearms, Ammunition, Militaria, Weapons and Knives</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Fireworks, Explosives and Explosive Substances</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Food</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Games Software: Sony, Sega, and Nintendo</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Government IDs and Licenses</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Hazardous, Restricted, and Perishable Items</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Human Parts and Remains</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>•</strong> Importation of Goods − examples include CDs that were intended only for distribution in a certain country</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> International Trading</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Items Encouraging Illegal Activity − examples include an eBook describing how to create methamphetamine</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Mature Audiences</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Medical Devices − examples include contact lenses, pacemakers, and surgical instruments</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Misleading Titles</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Mod Chips</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Movie Prints</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>•</strong> OEM Software</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Offensive Material − examples include ethnically or racially offensive material</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Police, Army, Navy and Air force Related Items</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Pre−Sale Listings</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Prohibited Services</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Promotional Items</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Real Estate</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Recordable Media</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>•</strong> Replica and Counterfeit Items</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Ringtones</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Stocks and Other Securities</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Stolen Property</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Surveillance Equipment</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Tobacco</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Trademarks</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Travel</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom10"><strong>•</strong> Weapons &amp; Knives</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom18"><strong>•</strong> Wine (also see Alcohol)</div><div class="rightPanelDesc paddingBottom8"><strong>5. Keyword Spamming Policy</strong></div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>5.1</strong> Keyword spamming occurs when Sellers place brand names or other inappropriate keywords in a title or description for the purpose of gaining attention or diverting members to a listing. Keyword spamming in listings is not permitted on BuynBrag.com. The text sellers place in listings must be directly relevant to the item being sold.</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>5.2</strong> Violations of this policy may result in a range of actions, including:</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall3 paddingBottom8"><strong>•</strong> Product Listing cancellation</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall3 paddingBottom8"><strong>•</strong> Limits on account privileges</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall3 paddingBottom8"><strong>•</strong> Account suspension</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall3 paddingBottom18"><strong>•</strong> Loss of Top Rated Seller status at BuynBrag.com</div><div class="rightPanelDesc paddingBottom8"><strong>6. Links Policy</strong></div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>6.1</strong> In general, when listing items on BuynBrag.com, Sellers can include links that are solely intended to provide additional details about the items. That means links should only be used in circumstances when that information can’t be included in the listing itself. These links include additional images, technical specifications, manufacturer warranties, and other information that can help buyers make an informed purchasing decision. Other links that point to a third-party provider’s Website are also allowed, such as image hosting sites, payment processors or courier companies.</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom18"><strong>6.2</strong> BuynBrag.com doesn’t allow links to non−BuynBrag sites or content where other items are offered for sale. BuynBrag continually reviews links on the site and reserves the right to block any link considered unsafe for our members. As a Seller, please make sure that your listing follows links policy of BuynBrag. If it doesn’t, it may be removed, and you may be subject to a range of other actions, including limits your selling privileges and/or suspension of your account.</div><div class="rightPanelDesc paddingBottom8"><strong>7. Rules about Intellectual Property</strong></div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>7.1</strong> BuynBrag is committed to protecting the intellectual property rights of third parties and to providing a safe marketplace to trade. Unauthorized use or Infringement of copyrighted material and trademarks are strictly prohibited at BuynBrag.</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>7.2</strong> BuynBrag has zero tolerance for any intellectual property violations. Counterfeits, unauthorized replicas, unauthorized items (such as counterfeit watches, handbags, or other accessories) or unauthorized copies (such as copies of software programs, video games, music albums, movies, television programs, or photographs) are not permitted at BuynBrag. Unauthorized copies include (but are not limited to) copies that are pirated, duplicated, backed−up or bootlegged. It is illegal to sell unauthorized copies of media.</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>7.3</strong> If the product you are selling bears the name or logo of a company, but it wasn’t made or endorsed by that company, don’t list it at BuynBrag.</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>7.4</strong> Academic software is software sold at significantly discounted prices to students, faculty members and educational institutions. Do not list academic copies of software At BuynBrag unless you are authorized to do so as an educational reseller, an educational institution a student or a faculty member.</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>7.5</strong> Beta software, test software and evaluation software are not permitted at BuynBrag. Beta, test, and evaluation copies of software are preliminary copies of software distributed by software developers strictly for the purpose of evaluation and troubleshooting.</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>7.6</strong> Do not list "OEM" or "bundled" copies of software At BuynBrag unless you are selling it with computer hardware. For Context, Original Equipment Manufacturer (OEM), or bundled software, is software that is obtained as part of the purchase of a new computer. OEM software licenses usually prohibit the purchaser from reselling the software without the computer or, in some cases, without any computer hardware.</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>7.7</strong> Bootleg recordings are unauthorized recordings of concerts or live performances. Sellers are not permitted to list bootleg recordings at BuynBrag.</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>7.8</strong> Violations of this policy may result in a range of actions, including:</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall3 paddingBottom8"><strong>•</strong> Product Listing cancellation</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall3 paddingBottom8"><strong>•</strong> Limits on account privileges</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall3 paddingBottom8"><strong>•</strong> Account suspension</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall3 paddingBottom18"><strong>•</strong> Loss of Top Rated Seller status at BuynBrag.com</div><div class="rightPanelDesc paddingBottom8"><strong>8. Pricing Policy</strong></div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom8"><strong>8.1</strong> Please note that trust is the most important aspect of trade between buyers and sellers in marketplace and one of the key aspects of trust is fair pricing. For healthy transaction flow at BuynBrag.com, we ask you to price your items responsibly.</div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom18"><strong>8.2</strong> Please note that we are constantly monitoring prices for each Seller at various channels and do not allow you to price your items at higher prices at BuynBrag.com vs. other channels such as your own retail store, your own Website (if any) or any other 3rd party retail stores or Websites. You should price your items sold at BuynBrag.com to be same as the lowest rate you are selling at elsewhere or even lower but it should not be more. Violation of our pricing policy will result into warning notices and can also result into account suspension and/or store suspension.</div><div class="rightPanelDesc paddingBottom8"><strong>9. Honesty in MRP</strong></div><div class="rightPanelDescSmall2 paddingBottom18"><strong>9.1</strong> Please note the trust you build with your buyers will go away if you artificially start showing higher MRP, so that the selling price appears to be much better deal vs. what it actually is. Artificially increasing MRP is strictly prohibited at BuynBrag.com and any violation will result into account suspension.</div></article></section></div></div></div></div></div><!-- ngSwitchWhen: contact --><!-- ngSwitchWhen: aboutUs --><!-- ngSwitchWhen: policies --><!-- ngSwitchWhen: trends --><!-- ngSwitchWhen: search --><!-- ngSwitchWhen: profileHeader --></div><div sign-up="" id="registe